  "prompt": "Why does stars are not showing in my clash of clans map when I win on fighting with the other random players ?",
  "response": "In *Clash of Clans*, when you attack other players in multiplayer battles (also known as \"raids\"), the stars you earn are only displayed on the Battle Log and not directly on your home village map. Here\u2019s why this happens and where you can see your stars:\n\n1. **Stars in Multiplayer Battles**:  \n   When you attack another player\u2019s village, the stars you earn (1, 2, or 3 stars) are recorded in your Battle Log. These stars indicate the success of your raid, but they don\u2019t appear visually on your home village map.\n\n2. **Home Village Map**:  \n   The stars shown on your home village map are for **defense**. They represent the stars lost when other players attack your village. If you successfully defend your village and the attacker doesn\u2019t earn any stars, your village map will remain intact.\n\n3. **Battle Log**:  \n   To see the stars you\u2019ve earned from your attacks, check your Battle Log. You can access it by tapping the \"Battle Log\" button (shield icon) on the bottom-left corner of your screen. This log shows your recent attacks and defenses, including the stars earned or lost.\n\nIf you\u2019re not seeing stars in your Battle Log after winning a raid, ensure you\u2019re checking the correct section (attacks, not defenses). Additionally, it\u2019s possible that the game didn\u2019t register your victory properly due to a connectivity issue or bug; restarting the game or ensuring a stable internet connection may help resolve this.\n\nLet me know if you have other questions! \ud83c\udff0\u2728",
